==Walkthrough==
[[File:Dorgeshuun_Tunnels.png|thumb|400px|A map of the tunnels.]]
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Sigmund]] on the {{FloorNumber|uk=1}} of the Lumbridge Castle. {{Chat option|1Do you have any quests for me?|1Yes}}
*Ask the following people about what happened in the cellar. You can stop when one mentions a goblin in the basement.
**[[Duke Horacio|Duke]] {{Chat option|3What happened in the cellar?}} ({{Chat option|4What happened in the cellar?}} if started Dragon Slayer)
**[[Cook_(Lumbridge)|Cook]] {{Chat option|5Do you know what happened in the castle cellar?}} ({{Chat option|2Do you know what happened in the castle cellar?}} if started recipe for disaster)
**[[Hans]] {{Chat option|1Do you know what happened in the cellar?}}
**[[Father Aereck]] {{Chat option|4Do you know what happened in the castle cellar?}}
**[[Bob]] {{Chat option|1Do you know what happened in the castle cellar?}}
**[[Gee]] or [[Donie]] {{Chat option|5Do you know what happened in the castle cellar?}}
*Talk to [[Duke Horacio|Duke]] again. {{Chat option|3The cook says he saw something in the cellar}} ({{Chat option|4The cook says he saw something in the cellar}} if started Dragon Slayer)
*Climb-down the trapdoor in the kitchen on the {{FloorNumber|uk=0}}.
*Use your [[pickaxe]] on the rubble in the basement and climb through the hole.
*Light your [[light source]] and grab the [[Brooch (The Lost Tribe)|brooch]].
*Show the brooch to the duke. {{Chat option|2Talk about something else.|3I dug through the rubble...}} or {{Chat option|4I dug through the rubble...}} or {{Chat option|3I dug through the rubble...}}
*Go to the [[Varrock Palace]] library in [[Varrock]].
* Talk to [[Reldo]]. {{Chat option|1}}
*Search the northern bookcase on the west wall for goblin symbol book.
*Read through the book.
*Go to [[Goblin Village]] and talk to the generals, and mediate for them until you learn goblin emotes. {{Chat option|1Have you ever heard of the Dorgeshuun?|3It doesn't really matter|2Well either way they refused to fight|3Well I found a brooch underground...|3Well why not show me both greetings?}}
*Go back to the Lumbridge Castle cellar and follow the map in the image on this page through the caves. Don't stray from it! (Clicking on the minimap also auto-paths the correct path)
*At the end of the cave talk to [[Mistag]], and do your [[Goblin Bow]] in front of him.
*Talk to Mistag then let him take you back to Lumbridge. {{Chat option|4Can you show me the way out of the mines?}}
*Talk to the duke. He won't believe you. {{Chat option|3I've made contact with the cave goblins...}} or {{Chat option|4I've made contact with the cave goblins...}}
*Pickpocket Sigmund and unlock his chest in the other room to find some [[HAM robes]]. Keep them for [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]].
*Go to the [[HAM Dungeon|HAM lair]] west of Lumbridge Castle.
*Pick the lock on the trapdoor and enter the lair.
*Search the crate south of the ladder to find the stolen [[silverware]].
*Bring the silverware to the duke. He will fire Sigmund and give you a signed peace treaty. {{Chat option|3I found the missing silverware in the HAM cave!}}
*Go into the basement again. Follow [[Kazgar]] to travel to Mistag. {{Chat option|2}}
*Talk to Mistag, with the peace treaty in your inventory, and a cutscene will play.}}

Quest complete!

